{
  "texts": [
    "To reduce computational costs, all simulation fields are downsampled to a resolution of 128 × 128.",
    "The saved quantities include fields of absolute pressure, density, temperature, signed skin friction, and tangential velocity gradients across the airfoil surface over a full pitching cycle.",
    "Figure 9 illustrates a spatio-temporal representation of the wall shear stress (τ w) across one complete pitching cycle, highlighting the pitch-up and pitch-down phases and demonstrating the structured mapping of surface data over time.",
    "We conclude the analysis of the proposed test cases by presenting additional comparisons and complete field prediction examples.",
    "We compute the 1D Wasserstein-1 distance to evaluate distributional differences."
